Notaspis tibialis
Nicolet, 1855
.

Description of juvenile stages . Larva oval (
Fig. 17
), light-yellow, in some individuals with darker region gla . Prodorsum subtriangular, seta ro rather long, setae le and in shorter, and inserted wider; all setae slightly curved and barbed; seta ex short and smooth. Bothridium rounded, sensillus rather short, clavate, with barbed head.

Prodorsal setae of tritonymph (
Fig. 20
) relatively longer than in larva, especially setae le and in ; in longer than ro and le ; all setae slightly curved and barbed, seta ex small and smooth. Bothridium rounded, sensillus clavate, with barbed head, slimmer than in larva.
